concepts.term: Common examples include fast low-angle shot (FLASH), fast imaging with steady precession (FISP), gradient-refocused acquisition in the steady state (GRASS), and steady-state free precession (SSFP)

evidence: gradient-echo sequences have no 180° refocusing pulse, and this allows shorter TE and TR values to be used.
